      <h1>Vibe Coding: Daily Strategic Pointers &amp; Logic Log</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Tracking the journey from Natural Language to Systemic Automation.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>📅 Phase 1: The Foundation (Workflow &amp; Control) - Days 1–8</h2>
    <dl>
      <dt><strong>Day 1 - The "Entry Point" Protocol (AGENTS.md / GEMINI.md)</strong></dt>
      <dd><em>Pointer:</em> Create a <code>GEMINI.md</code> in your root folder as the AI's "Mission Briefing." The CLI searches for it automatically, eliminating Prompt Drift. <em>ID Application:</em> Define your Voice (Senior ID) and Pedagogy (Bloom's, QM).</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 2 - The "Skeleton-First" Prompt</strong></dt>
      <dd><em>Pointer:</em> Demand a project architecture before any code. Use <code>/plan</code> to force the AI to check logic against your briefing first. <em>ID Application:</em> Ask for a 15-week module map before individual page content.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 3 - The "Draft-to-Diff" Workflow</strong></dt>
      <dd><em>Pointer:</em> Request changes in Diff format to avoid total rewrites that lose academic tone. Fix specific items like aria-labels or CSS classes. <em>ID Application:</em> Audit existing Canvas pages without overwriting subject matter text.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 4 - "Prompt Injection" for Standards</strong></dt>
      <dd><em>Pointer:</em> Use <code>@</code> or <code>/path</code> to feed the AI specific reference documents. Provide the "Answer Key" (Brand Guide, Syllabus Template) so the AI doesn't guess. <em>ID Application:</em> Inject the official syllabus template before generating a new draft.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 5 - The "Self-Documenting" Loop</strong></dt>
      <dd><em>Pointer:</em> End every session by asking the AI to summarize its successful steps into a "Skill" for your library. Turns a one-time success into a repeatable SOP.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 6 - The "Multi-Agent Debate"</strong></dt>
      <dd><em>Pointer:</em> Simulate a "Committee Review" - ask the AI to role-play as Student, Auditor, and SME simultaneously. <em>ID Application:</em> Pressure-test a module's navigation and cognitive load.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 7 - The "Raw-to-Refined" Proxy (The Lynx Strategy)</strong></dt>
      <dd><em>Pointer:</em> Use <code>!lynx -dump [URL] | gemini</code> to process raw data before designing. Fast-track turning a 50-page PDF into clean Learning Objectives.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 8 - The "Modular Skill" (Atomic SOPs)</strong></dt>
      <dd><em>Pointer:</em> Build a <code>02_Skills</code> folder of small, task-specific Markdown files. <em>Action:</em> <code>Run: /path ./02_Skills/AltText_Reviewer.md</code> then <code>gemini "Run this skill on index.html."</code></dd>
    </dl>

    <h2>📅 Phase 2: Agentic ID Mastery (Context &amp; Alignment) - Days 9–12</h2>
    <dl>
      <dt><strong>Day 9 - The "Semantic Cross-Check" (Alignment)</strong></dt>
      <dd>Use the CLI to verify alignment between Assessments and Learning Objectives. Finds "Orphaned Objectives" (taught but not tested). Ensures QM standards for Alignment.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 10 - The "Cognitive Load Audit" (Density Check)</strong></dt>
      <dd>Audit the "Visual Weight" and word counts of Canvas pages. Identifies walls of text or high link density that increase learner frustration.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 11 - Prompt Injection for Brand Compliance</strong></dt>
      <dd>Feed the AI your CSS stylesheet before asking for HTML design. Forces local hex codes and styles instead of generic colors.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 12 - The "Predictive Syllabus" (Contextual Mapping)</strong></dt>
      <dd>Map a "Project Timeline" from a single Syllabus PDF. Predict high-workload weeks and suggest "Low-Friction" design for weeks with heavy assessments.</dd>
    </dl>

    <h2>📅 Phase 3: Continuous Optimization (Scale &amp; Sustainability) - Days 13–31</h2>
    <dl>
      <dt><strong>Day 13 - The "Accessibility Regression" Protocol</strong></dt><dd>Compare updated files against an Accessibility Baseline automatically after every change.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 14 - The "Synthetic Student" Simulation (Agentic UX)</strong></dt><dd>Use specific profiles as Agentic Personas to stress-test course navigation.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 15 - The "Automated Indexing" Habit</strong></dt><dd>Auto-update <code>master_file_index.md</code> after every major architectural change - Documentation-as-Code.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 16 - The "Environment-Aware" Pre-Flight Check</strong></dt><dd>Force the Agent to define its Environmental Assumptions before outputting code. Catches missing CDNs or CSS conflicts.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 17 - The "Full-Vault Synthesis" (MCP Integration)</strong></dt><dd>Use the Model Context Protocol to bridge your research vault directly into your CLI.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 18 - Multiple Means of Action &amp; Expression (The "HOW")</strong></dt><dd>Focus on how students demonstrate mastery. Vary response methods and ensure all interactives are keyboard navigable.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 19 - The "Agentic Git" (Instructional Assets as Code)</strong></dt><dd>Manage instructional assets as versioned GitHub repositories. Treat Canvas HTML snippets as "Instructional Software."</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 20 - The "Semantic Bridge" (Historical Knowledge Extraction)</strong></dt><dd>Extract "Latent Knowledge" from Archives to inform current projects.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 21 - The "Self-Correction Pattern" (Agentic Reflection)</strong></dt><dd>Prompt the AI to audit its own output against a specific constraint before the final reveal.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 22 - The "Multi-Modal Audit" (Vision-to-Text)</strong></dt><dd>Use vision capabilities to audit visual Brand Alignment and Visual Weight.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 23 - The "Constraint-Based Prompt" (Guardrail Logic)</strong></dt><dd>Explicitly list what the AI cannot do before defining the task.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 24 - The "Pedagogical Alignment Agent" (Bloom's Auditor)</strong></dt><dd>Audit the "Verbs" in your objectives against Bloom's Taxonomy levels. Flag under-assessed outcomes.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 25 - The "Synthetic SME" (Context Injection)</strong></dt><dd>A "Shadow SME" persona reviews your instructional tone and technical accuracy.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 26 - The "Accessibility Unit Test" (Failure Injection)</strong></dt><dd>Deliberately introduce a "break" in a component and ask the AI to find it.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 27 - The "Vibe-to-SOP" (Auto-Documentation)</strong></dt><dd>Convert a successful session into a Standard Operating Procedure immediately.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 28 - The "Ergonomic Flow" Persona (Workflow Adaptation)</strong></dt><dd>Suggest "Low-Strokes" alternatives for complex tasks using pre-built utility classes.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 29 - The "Legacy-to-Logic" Pipeline (Course Migration)</strong></dt><dd>Strip formatting from old courses and convert them into structured JSON "Skeletons."</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 30 - The "Course-Specific Memory" Anchor (NotebookLM Bridge)</strong></dt><dd>Use persistent context to keep Course-Specific Context alive across development cycles.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 31 - The "Session Pruning" Protocol</strong></dt><dd>Explicitly clear the AI's working memory between unrelated tasks to prevent logic bleeding.</dd>
    </dl>

    <h2>📅 Phase 4: Systemic Engineering &amp; Institutional Scaling - Days 32–40</h2>
    <dl>
      <dt><strong>Day 32 - The "Schema-Driven" ID (JSON Architect)</strong></dt><dd>Move from writing Prompt Instructions to defining Data Schemas.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 33 - The "Context-Pruning" Strategy (Token Efficiency)</strong></dt><dd>Periodically "Summarize and Compress" chat history into a new <code>MISSION_UPDATE.md</code>.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 34 - The "Pedagogical Shadowing" (ARIA-Mirroring)</strong></dt><dd>Generate the "Invisible Layer" of the course (ARIA labels) as a separate build step.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 35 - The "Voice-to-Logic" Pipeline (Ergonomic Level-Up)</strong></dt><dd>Dictate intent; let the AI convert it into complex CLI commands.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 36 - The "Course-as-API" Concept</strong></dt><dd>Treat your course modules as End-points that can be queried by AI Agents.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 37 - Automated Rubric Calibration (The Fairness Audit)</strong></dt><dd>Compare a Syllabus, Rubric, and Sample Assignment simultaneously for alignment.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 38 - The "Cross-Model" Consensus (Model Diversity Audit)</strong></dt><dd>Run the same audit through two models and generate a "Conflict Report."</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 39 - Bilingual Sync (ZH/EN Content Mirroring)</strong></dt><dd>Maintain a "Semantic Mirror" between English and Chinese materials.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 40 - The "Recursive Workspace" (Self-Evolving Manual)</strong></dt><dd>Audit your manual against your actual log. Extract finalized decisions into a concise instruction set.</dd>
    </dl>

    <h2>📅 Phase 5: Institutional Leadership &amp; AI Governance - Days 41–60</h2>
    <dl>
      <dt><strong>Day 41 - The "Institutional AI Manifesto" (Policy as Code)</strong></dt><dd>Treat AI usage policies as "Guardrail Systems" injected into every prompt.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 42 - The "Accessibility Debt" Calculator</strong></dt><dd>Estimate "Correction Hours" needed for legacy courses based on audit results.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 43 - Inter-Departmental Knowledge Graph</strong></dt><dd>Find semantic connections between different departmental materials.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 44 - The "Syllabus-to-Skill" Auto-Pipeline</strong></dt><dd>Automatically convert Course Policies into a Markdown-based Agentic Skill.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 45 - The "Context-Aware" Scheduling Agent (Workflow Resilience)</strong></dt><dd>Feed your project energy cycles into the CLI to optimize high-focus tasks.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 46 - The "Multi-Persona Focus Group" (Synthetic Stakeholders)</strong></dt><dd>Run a course through a focus group of different AI personas simultaneously.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 47 - The "Prompt Versioning" Protocol (Instructional Reliability)</strong></dt><dd>Track your prompts in Git to ensure consistency over time.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 48 - The "Shadow ID" Agent (Peer Reviewer)</strong></dt><dd>An Agent specifically tasked with being your "Cynical Peer Reviewer."</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 49 - Data-Driven Feedback Loop (LRS Integration)</strong></dt><dd>Analyze student interaction data against your design choices.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 50 - The "Half-Century" System Audit</strong></dt><dd>Audit your entire infrastructure for "Instructional Debt."</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 51 - The "Voice-to-Blueprint" Workflow (Efficient Design)</strong></dt><dd>Dictate a course overview; AI generates a full 15-week Blueprint.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 52 - The "Compliance Crawler" (Institutional Scrutiny)</strong></dt><dd>Batch audit 10+ folders to check for brand drift.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 53 - The "Cross-Platform Mirroring" (Canvas-to-Rise)</strong></dt><dd>Convert LMS page content into Articulate Rise-compatible Markdown.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 54 - The "Efficiency-Balanced" AI Agent (Logic Balancing)</strong></dt><dd>An Agent that suggests "Automation Shortcuts" based on session length.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 55 - The "Generative Feedback" Rubric-Bot</strong></dt><dd>Feed Rubric and sample submission; AI generates feedback drafts.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 56 - "Agentic Procurement" (VPAT Auditor)</strong></dt><dd>Audit a vendor's accessibility statement before purchasing software.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 57 - "Translation Reliability" (EN/ZH Semantic Check)</strong></dt><dd>Check if bilingual notes retain legal and technical nuances.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 58 - "Historical Context" Bridge (Long-Term Memory)</strong></dt><dd>Bridge your archive into current sessions to avoid past mistakes.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 59 - The "Zero-Keystroke" Ideal (Voice-to-Course)</strong></dt><dd>Build an entire module using ONLY voice commands.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 60 - The "Full-Cycle" Systemic Audit</strong></dt><dd>Synthesize Days 1–60. Rewrite your manual to reflect your new role as Systemic Engineer.</dd>
    </dl>

    <h2>📅 Phase 6: Advanced Orchestration &amp; Structural Integrity - Days 61–80</h2>
    <dl>
      <dt><strong>Day 61 - The "Self-Healing" Syllabus (Integrity Logic)</strong></dt><dd>Monitor your syllabus for dead links or outdated dates and auto-repair them.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 62 - Multi-Model Adversarial Auditing</strong></dt><dd>Run code through two competing models and have them "debate" the outcome.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 63 - The "SME Voice" Fine-Tuning</strong></dt><dd>Use RAG to ensure generated announcements match specific faculty tone.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 64 - Semantic Data Migration</strong></dt><dd>Map previous course goals to current industry trends automatically.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 65 - The "Agentic" Onboarding SOP</strong></dt><dd>Build an Agent that can train a new hire on your specific workflow.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 66 - "Effort Mapping" (Workflow Budgeting)</strong></dt><dd>Estimate total work required and suggest automation to lower the manual budget.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 67 - Vision-to-Vibe (Layout Audit)</strong></dt><dd>Upload a screenshot to audit white space and visual hierarchy.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 68 - The "Institutional Memory" RAG</strong></dt><dd>Create a vault for "Failed Projects" to avoid repeating historical mistakes.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 69 - Zero-Friction Synthesis</strong></dt><dd>Merge Word docs and JSON files into single, accessible HTML pages.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 70 - Ethical AI Auditing for Diversity</strong></dt><dd>Audit your case studies for balanced representation.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 71 - The "Cross-Platform" Sync</strong></dt><dd>Ensure your local notes and GitHub snippets are semantically aligned.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 72 - Agentic "Help Desk" Simulation</strong></dt><dd>Use the AI to ask confusion questions to test your own instructions.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 73 - The "Rubric Stress-Test"</strong></dt><dd>Ask the AI to grade sample papers to check for rubric bias.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 74 - Voice-to-JSON Course Blueprints</strong></dt><dd>Dictate the logic of a term; AI outputs a JSON blueprint for ingestion.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 75 - Advanced Component Generation</strong></dt><dd>Generate components with built-in ARIA state management.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 76 - The "Course Lifecycle" Agent</strong></dt><dd>Track the "Age" of assets and flag content for review.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 77 - Predictive Accessibility Regression</strong></dt><dd>Predict which pages will fail compliance if a global style changes.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 78 - The "Systemic Librarian"</strong></dt><dd>Reorganize your skills folder based on actual usage frequency in your logs.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 79 - Collaborative Agentic Editing</strong></dt><dd>Moderate a session between two agents with different pedagogical goals.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 80 - The "Strategic Briefing" Generator</strong></dt><dd>Turn technical logs into high-level executive summaries for leadership.</dd>
    </dl>

    <h2>📅 Phase 7: The "Endgame" &amp; Sustained Resilience - Days 81–100</h2>
    <dl>
      <dt><strong>Day 81 - The "Long-Tail" Accessibility Audit</strong></dt><dd>Find "Edge Case" issues like nested iframe titles.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 82 - Energy-Aware Task Prioritization</strong></dt><dd>An Agent that re-orders your tasks based on your current project bandwidth.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 83 - Semantic Archive Pruning</strong></dt><dd>Identify and archive notes that are no longer true due to regulatory updates.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 84 - The "Shadow ID" Agent (Peer Reviewer)</strong></dt><dd>Ask the AI to be your most critical reviewer before a final reveal.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 85 - The "Zero-Draft" Strategy</strong></dt><dd>Generate 5 different pedagogical approaches; select the winner and discard the rest.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 86 - Cross-Contextual Learning</strong></dt><dd>Find ways your study notes directly improve your current operational SOPs.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 87 - The "Visual Hierarchy" Vision Audit</strong></dt><dd>Analyze the "Gaze Path" of a page to ensure focus on critical information.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 88 - Institutional SOP Versioning</strong></dt><dd>Compare previous manuals with current logs and auto-merge best practices.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 89 - Automation-First Refactoring</strong></dt><dd>Refactor legacy code using an automation-first mindset to eliminate technical debt.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 90 - Automated Grade-to-Goal Alignment</strong></dt><dd>Audit gradebook weights against learning objective importance.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 91 - The "Expert Learner" Simulation</strong></dt><dd>Critique how much "Support" you can safely remove for expert learners.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 92 - The "Keystroke Economy" Review</strong></dt><dd>Audit your logs for manual commands that should have been aliases.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 93 - Voice-Command Optimization</strong></dt><dd>Create phonetically distinct aliases to make dictation smoother.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 94 - The "Multi-Modal" Executive Brief</strong></dt><dd>Turn your index into a short audio briefing for your morning routine.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 95 - Legacy System Decommissioning</strong></dt><dd>Identify and delete redundant files that have been logic-migrated.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 96 - The "Agentic Feedback Loop"</strong></dt><dd>An Agent that monitors your sessions and suggests new automation opportunities.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 97 - Predictive Resource Allocation</strong></dt><dd>Predict support spikes based on course complexity throughout the term.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 98 - Cross-Vault Synthesis</strong></dt><dd>Link personal administration and professional projects into a single success metric.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 99 - The "Mission Critical" Review</strong></dt><dd>Audit your briefing one last time to ensure it reflects your senior leadership role.</dd>
      <dt><strong>Day 100 - Total Systemic Integration</strong></dt><dd>The culmination. Build a dashboard that manages all 100 days of logic. <code>gemini "Final Task: Integrate all 100 days of logic into a single Exoskeleton Dashboard."</code></dd>
    </dl>

